1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
In this lesson, we will cover how to customize the search results template.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,000
When visitors on your site search for content, they are taken to a search results page,

3
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:14,000
and the search results template determines how this page and the results are structured.

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:20,000
I am using the Twenty Twenty-Four theme and this is the default layout for results.

5
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:26,000
We can customize the search results page by editing the template.

6
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:31,000
So to do this, let's make our way to the dashboard, click on Appearance, and then open up the Site Editor.

7
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Click on Templates, and then select the search results template.

8
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:46,000
You can add a unique header and footer to the template, or you may wish to change how results are displayed via the Query Loop block.

9
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Let's open the List view to gain a better understanding of the page structure.

10
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Firstly, you can decide if you want to keep or remove the Search Results title.

11
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:05,000
If you keep it, you have a choice to show the search term in the title or not.

12
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,000
And you may choose to style the block further.

13
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,000
In this example, I am going to customize how my searchresults are displayed.

14
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:25,000
So the first step is to select the Query Loop block, which is used to display results.

15
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:31,000
I am going to select a different pattern for my Query Loop block.

16
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:35,000
So to do this, I will use my Block Toolbar and click on Replace.

17
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:40,000
This allows you to select a different pattern.

18
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:46,000
And I am going to select the pattern called Small Image and Title.

19
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:54,000
Now I will go ahead and modify the Query Loop block further.

20
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,000
Firstly, let's change the alignment to Wide Width.

21
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,000
Next, I will add a Post Excerpt block below the title.

22
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:07,000
Once added, I will select the right column in the List View.

23
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:16,000
And then change the vertical alignment to align top.

24
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:23,000
As I want the title and the excerpt to align with the top of the image.

25
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,000
Next, I am going to select the post featured image.

26
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Open Styles and then change the aspect ratio of the Post Featured Image block to 3x4

27
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:42,000
to ensure uniformity and that all the images are the same size.

28
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:51,000
Then we can hit Save and check out our new search results page on the front-end.

29
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Once again, I will search for some content.

30
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:00,000
But this time, the results display in a new format due to modifying the search results template.

31
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:06,000
To undo the changes, click on the three vertical dots next to the name and select Clear Customizations.

32
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,000
And this will revert back to the original state of the template.

33
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:21,000
All the best as you decide how you want your search results to be displayed.

